	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>By level 10 you should have some leather or raw hide armor pieces.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some of the stuff you can quest for. Otherwise, buy or tailor some of it.  Also, you should be pretty much done with your newbie issued weapon and have replaced it with a rusty one or better.  If soloing is not working out then try grouping for a bit until you get used to using songs.<br><br>One common problem I had was using Chords of Dissonence.  It kept pulling adds on me that I didn't want.  So, I got some throwing knives and pulled with those off to the side of the orc hill region.  Greatly reduced the number of adds.  I stopped using CoD and stuck with twisting Hymn of Restoration with J's Whistling Warsong. <br><br>Get a shield. It helps.<br><br>If you hit 2 bubs of health turn on Selo's and run away.  Don't wait till you get down to one because even with Selo's the orcs can keep up with you at that point.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
