	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 10th 9:25 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It may seem insignificant but there is an item most everyone knows of and every Rogue and Bard will have at some point called the Mask of Deception. Nice piece of gear giving +13 cha and is clickable to change you into a Dark Elf. It is IMPERATIVE if you want this mask to work that your DEITY (which is unchangeable without rerolling your character) Should be agnostic! There are some other deities that may allow you access to all races but agnostic is safest. I started my first character as a Bard (now retired at 52) being unaware of any race changing ability I chose Quellious. About 20 or so levels later when I put on my mask and attempted to enter Neriak and was killed by the guards I realized my mistake. If you go agnostic and get these masks you can complete most any quest just as an enchanter can! But if you chose a deity your faction is skewed for the life of your character.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hopefully this little info saves atleast 1 person from messing up as I did. I imagine I would have enjoyed my bard alot more If I could have quested with those masks, oh well.<br><br>Anyone know of any 'safe' deities that will not put you at odds with someone. Maybe Veeshan?<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
