	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been experimenting with a Vah Shir bard. He is level 11 now.&nbsp;&nbsp;I like him for soloing.  True, necro's or druids would be better soloing but I am not a big fan of root/nuke strategy.  Its too easy and I want a challenge.  Tried it. Just didn't like it.  So, now, on to the bard, the only class in 2 and half years that I have not played at all (tried to others to at least level 20).  I won't give up my rogue (my favorite) or my monk.  I like the play styles.  But I enjoy my bard very much so far.  Particulary, I like the reduced down time for heals and meditation.  I like the speed of traveling.  So far I have soloed all but level 8.  Then, I grouped only because I got lonesome and wanted company.  I like the monk's lower down time but frankly, I like finding and buying gear, too.  I like stuff.  So the bard gives me that - soloing, grouping, and an excuse for stuff.  I could go on but that covers the major points.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
