	   <a name=101785867751938></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101785867751938><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101785867751938>RE: Bards CAN solo</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101785867751938#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=140616><span id=Guru>Victorex</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>58 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 3rd 1:31 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here are my 2cp's worth:<br><br>I have multiple characters, one of which is a 15th level bard. I also have a monk and a ranger as you will see in my posting below. There is some really good information on the formulas used to calculate damage at www.monkly-business.com. This information is monk specific, but the damage bonus section and how it calculates is accurate for just about all classes. I'll sum up the major points in this post with the formulas (hope you are up for some math :).<br><br>Basically your damage bonus works like this for one handed weapons:<br><br>Base Damage Bonus = (Your level - 25)/3<br><br>So, you won't get a damage bonus on any weapon until you are level 28.<br><br>BDB = (28 - 25)/3<br>BDB = (3)/3<br>BDB = 1<br><br>After you attain level 28, you will see your 1 handed damage bonus increase every 3 levels. <br><br>Now, the damage bonus on 2 handed weapons was recently changed. 2 handed weapons get an additional modifier based on their delay. The formulas are as follows:<br><br>For 2 handed weapons with a delay &lt;= 27<br><br>Damage Bonus = One handed damage bonus + 1<br><br>So you have to calculate your 1 handed bonus using the first formula, then add 1 to that.<br><br>For 2 handed weapons with a delay &gt;= 28 and &lt;= 39:<br><br>Damage Bonus = One handed Damage Bonus + (Level -27) / 4<br><br>For 2 handed weapons with a delay &gt;= 40and &lt;= 42<br><br>Damage Bonus = One handed Damage Bonus + ((Level -27) / 4) + 1<br><br>For 2 handed weapons with a delay &gt; 42<br><br>Damage Bonus = One handed Damage Bonus + ((Level -27) / 4) + (Weapon Dly - 34) / 3<br><br>Keep in mind that this damage is added to your hit AFTER your maximum damage for that hit is calculated. There is another set of calcuations to figure what your max hit can be, then you add your damage bonus to get your maximum damage with that weapon. Keep in mind that the mob's ac can deduct from this damage, but in a long enough fight against an even con mob you will see hits for your maximum. Ok, here is the max damage formula:<br><br>Max Damage: Primary<br><br>Max Damage = Weapon Damage * ((Str + Weapon Skill) / 100) + Damage Bonus<br><br>So, my level 15 bard, while twisting Anthem and Jonathan's Whistling Warsong will see the following damage:<br><br>Str (with songs going) = 127<br>Skill (maxed at lvl 15) = 80 for 1hs<br>Weapon damage (Centi SS) = 12<br>Damage bonus (he is less than 28) = 0<br><br>Plug these in and you get:<br><br>Max Damage = 12 * ((127 + 80)/100) + 0<br>Max Damage = 12 * ((207)/100) + 0<br>Max Damage = 12 * 2.07 + 0<br>Max Damage = 24.84 + 0<br><br>Now, if you have this weapon combo, you won't see a hit greater than 24 at level 15. That's because there is a cap on your damage modifier prior to level 20. Let's look at the same bard at level 31.<br><br>Str = 127<br>Skill (if maxed) = 155<br>Weapon Damage = 12 (same Centi SS)<br>Damage Bonus = (31 - 25)/3 = 2<br><br>Plug these in to the formula and you get:<br><br>Max Damage = 12 * ((127 + 155)/100) + 2<br>Max Damage = 12 * (282/100) + 2<br>Max Damage = 12 * 2.82 + 2<br>Max Damage = 33.84 + 2<br>Max Damage = 35.84<br><br>I hope this clears up any questions. Also, keep in mind that the damage bonus only applies to your primary hand weapon. Offhand weapon calculations are done without the additional damage modifier on the end.<br><br>I also have the dual wield and double attack calculations if anyone is interested. Based on my experience, these formulas are very accurate. <br><br>Again, this information is posted in www.monkly-business.com. Some of the formulas on that site are monk-particular, but if you know the skill caps for your class then you can adapt the formula for your character.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr&nbsp;&nbsp;3 13:33:19 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 54 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
